Dear developers,

I just downloaded jakarta-tomcat-connectors-4.1.27-src.tar.gz to build the JK
connector and was faced to a typo in the file jk/native/common/jk_uri_worker_map.c

Here is the patch I used to complete the build process:
<------------ cut here --------------->
--- jk/native/common/jk_uri_worker_map.c.orig   Thu Oct  9 11:54:06 2003
+++ jk/native/common/jk_uri_worker_map.c        Thu Oct  9 11:53:35 2003
@@ -489,7 +489,7 @@
         unsigned i;
         unsigned best_match = -1;
         unsigned longest_match = 0;
-        char * clean_uri = jk_pool_strdup(&uw_map->tp,uri);;
+        char * clean_uri = jk_pool_strdup(&uw_map->tp,uri);
         char *url_rewrite = strstr(clean_uri, JK_PATH_SESSION_IDENTIFIER);

         if(url_rewrite) {

<------------ cut here --------------->

Hope I didn't waste your time with a well known issue... If it is the case, just
forget about it.

Regards,

Raphaël
